## Running Tests

### Commands

```bash
# Run all tests
rails test

# Run specific test file
rails test test/models/article_test.rb

# Run specific test
rails test test/models/article_test.rb:10
# (line 10 is where the test starts)

# Run tests matching pattern
rails test test/models

# Run system tests only
rails test:system

# Run with verbose output
rails test -v

# Run in parallel (faster)
rails test -j 4

# Run with backtrace
rails test -b
```

### Continuous Testing

```bash
# Install guard (auto-run tests on file changes)
gem 'guard-minitest', group: :development

# Generate Guardfile
guard init minitest

# Run guard
guard
```

